name: guanosine
description: A purine nucleoside in which guanine is attached to ribofuranose via a beta-N(9)-glycosidic bond.

name: 8-hydroxy-2'-deoxyguanosine
description: Guanosine substituted at the purine 8-position by a hydroxy group. It is used as a biomarker of oxidative DNA damage.

name: O-(alpha-D-mannose-1-phosphoryl)-L-serine
description: A mannose phosphate in which in which the phosphate group of alpha-D-mannose 1-phosphate is esterified by the alcoholic hydroxy group of L-serine.

name: glycyrrhizinic acid
description: A  triterpenoid saponin that is the  glucosiduronide derivative of 3beta-hydroxy-11-oxoolean-12-en-30-oic acid.
